details.purpose: Intended for recording details of Briganti Risk Score for prostate cancer.
details.use: Use to capture details and total scores under Briganti Risk score.

items.items: The Briganti risk score is a score for predicting probabilities of survival, recurrence, lymph node involvement, organ-defined involvement, extracapsular extension and seminal invasion.
A specific date and/or time which may be explicitly defined in a template or at run-time.
Patient age when risk score is calculated.
PSA level from laboratory report before the biopsy.

Clinical tumor stage is determined by digital rectal examination and does not include stages determined by imaging studies. What was your clinical tumor stage, using the AJCC Version 7/2010 Staging System? Note: Although it is possible to be stage TX or stage T4, this nomogram is not applicable for these stages.

Number of positive cores taken during biopsy. Information on cores taken at biopsy is optional. The nomogram can provide predictions without this information if not available. However, using this information, the nomogram can provide more refined predictions.

Number of negative cores taken during biopsy. Information on cores taken at biopsy is optional. The nomogram can provide predictions without this information if not available. However, using this information, the nomogram can provide more refined predictions.
What percentage of the biopsy samples taken were positive?
Probability of cancer-specific survival for 10 years after radical prostatectomy.
Probability of cancer-specific survival for 15 years after radical prostatectomy.
Progression-free probability for 5 years after radical prostatectomy.
Progression-free probability for 10 years after radical prostatectomy.
This number shows, as a percentage, the probability that the cancer will be found to be confined to the prostate gland when the prostate is removed.
This number shows, as a percentage, the probability of âextracapsular extension,â meaning the probability that the cancer extends through the capsule of the prostate into the surrounding tissue.
This number shows, as a percentage, the probability that prostate cancer has spread to the pelvic lymph nodes.

This number shows, as a percentage, the probability of âseminal vesicle invasion,â which occurs when prostate cancer has spread into the seminal vesicles â glands attached to the prostate that help to produce semen. This number shows the probability that the cancer has spread to one or both seminal vesicles.
Description of any incidental factors that may have contributed to the score.
Additional information required to capture local content or to align with other reference models/formalisms.
e.g. Local information requirements or additional metadata to align with FHIR or CIMI equivalents.
Primary, secondary and tertiary Gleason grades and Total Gleason score.
